    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion </strong>with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min or until softened but not coloured</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>700ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1L]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the<strong> </strong>pan and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry</p><p>Add your<strong> vegetable stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the risotto is cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!) and set aside for garnish</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, squeeze in the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and the<strong> grated cheese</strong> to the pan and stir to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>lemony risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a high heat. Once melted, drain your <strong>jumbo prawns</strong> then add to the pan with the <strong>remaining garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until the jumbo prawns are cooked through \u2013 these are your <strong>garlic jumbo prawns &</strong> <strong>courgette</strong>.</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and stir through most of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save some for garnish!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-courgette-and-jumbo-king-prawn-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlic jumbo prawns & courgette</strong> over the<strong> lemony risotto</strong></p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lemon wedge</strong>, <strong>lemon zest </strong>and the <strong>reserved chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
